  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).",
    "Toast 2-3 slices of bread until lightly browned and crumbly.",
    "Soak the bulgur in water for 30 minutes, then drain.",
    "In a large skillet, heat the butter over medium heat.",
    "Add the sliced shallots and cook until softened, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add the soaked bulgur, red wine vinegar, olive oil, and salt to the skillet.",
    "Stir to combine, then cook for 2-3 minutes.",
    "Stir in the chopped parsley and vin santo.",
    "Serve the kisir mixture over the toasted bread, garnished with additional parsley if desired.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy.",
    "Note: You can also make this recipe in a ceramic tagine on the stovetop or in the oven."
